body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

`./yosys -p "techmap -map tm.v" top.v -f "verilog -icells"`

`top.v`:
```
module top(input [31:0] A, input [4:0] B, output Y);
\$shiftx #(.A_WIDTH(32), .B_WIDTH(5), .A_SIGNED(0), .B_SIGNED(0), .Y_WIDTH(1)) u0 (.A(A), .B(B), .Y(Y));
endmodule
```

`tm.v`:
```
module \$shiftx (A, B, Y);
  parameter A_SIGNED = 0;
  parameter B_SIGNED = 0;
  parameter A_WIDTH = 500;
  parameter B_WIDTH = 1;
  parameter Y_WIDTH = 1;

  input [A_WIDTH-1:0] A;
  input [B_WIDTH-1:0] B;
  output [Y_WIDTH-1:0] Y;

  wire [A_WIDTH-1:0] A_forward;
  assign A_forward[A_WIDTH-1] = A[WIDTH-1];
endmodule
```


## Expected behavior

No infinite loop. 

## Actual behavior

Infinite loop. I actually missed the warning message because of all the other logging.

